ots and stalks and chilli (optional) into mixing bowl and chop <b>6 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and repeat chopping if necessary until a paste consistency is achieved."},{"content":"Add curry powder and oil and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add coconut milk, water and capsicum. Place Varoma into position and weigh mussels into it. Steam <b>7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Toss mussels in the Varoma dish to ensure even cooking and steam for a further <b>7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Distribute mussels evenly between two serving bowls and discard any mussels that have not opened during cooking."},{"content":"Add fish sauce and lime juice to mixing bowl and combine <b>6 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Pour sauce over mussels and garnish with fresh coriander leaves. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can substitute 4 cardamom pods with 1 tsp ground cardamom","Try making coconut milk for this recipe in your Thermomix - you'll be amazed at how fresh, simple and cost effective it is. Visit the official Thermomix Recipe Community (recipecommunity.com.au) for a free recipe.","Serve with crusty bread or steamed rice.","Leftover mussels can be shelled and tossed through a salad, stir-fry or pasta the following day.","Use any leftover sauce as a base for a fish or seafood curry.","If you make your own, use any leftover coconut milk in the <em>Coconut and quinoa porridge with toasted almonds<\/em> for breakfast the next morning."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","2 portions"]}